track.name: I Want to Talk About You
comments: picture a bar in your mind. it's late night. the light is low. you're with someone special. it's raining outside, you can hear it. couples walk along the street sharing a single opened umbrella. the weather is cold but you feel all warm, you and your company. this song is playing on the background, the bar is almost empty. both of you are drinking some wine. and oh yes, you're sure talking about her.
Newport is just sublime. Sat here on Christmas Eve giving it a listen.
My ears tell me it's Coltrane
I use to own this gem on LP the Great tenor player Ralph Moore use to work in disco mat and said to me "Hey Alfonzo get this one" He was never wrong. Love Trane, Love Ralph Moore. Peace
Good lord, I love this song ... Newport version is imprinted on my brain forever.
holy shit, the newport version of this is amazing
perfect love casts out all fear
